highlights.description: Judy talks about what drives her as a journalist
Dylan talks about learning the power of listening and taking people seriously while his dad was pleading with the city to hold on and own the Lincoln Schoolhouse property
Joe talks about how journalism allows him to talk with people
Joe remarks that public officials in Madison are willing to talk with reporters.
Cat tells a story about jumping at the chance to move back to Madison because of the rich arts environment here
Chelsea talks about the difficulty of affording to buy a house in Madison. Interesting contrast to perceptions of "the media" being part of an urban economic elite group.
Dylan remarks that people in Madison might be surprised by what Trump supporters are like
Dylan remarks on the power of actually stopping to listen
